\end{tabular}
\end{center}
All four priors give hit fractions in $0.23\%$--$0.47\%$, with fold variation $2.04$. No prior raises the hit fraction above $1\%$.

\subsection{Loose null-model test and filter sensitivity}
\label{sec:filter}

Broadening the comparison from $m_s$ alone to $\mathcal{F}^2$ against all five quark species $\{m_u, m_d, m_s, m_c, m_b\}$ (restricted to $n=2$ for dimensional consistency) yields $p_{\text{loose}} = 0.4748\%$, identical to $p_{\text{tight}}$, because $\mathcal{F}^2 \approx 95$~MeV is well outside the charm and bottom ranges at any reasonable scale, and too large for $m_u$ or $m_d$. The breakdown is shown in Table~\ref{tab:loose}.

